    "body": "Good point, I didn't really intend to replace the old system, but it was more like a quick workaround-ish solution, although I have to admit, I don't like having a conversion table _and_ still be required specify data types (e.g. `get_str()`, `get_int()`, ...).\n\nI pushed three more conservative and similar, but slightly different each, approaches:\n- [modularization-json-conversion-3](https://github.com/dexX7/bitcoin/commit/4aee62ad96232074685df1d41cb33a1baec746c6): one function to add new entries\n- [modularization-json-conversion-2](https://github.com/dexX7/bitcoin/commit/c614786f176d9a9dcf83bc1b960d153dbf29f56b): expose conversion class and table without param class\n- [modularization-json-conversion-1](https://github.com/dexX7/bitcoin/commit/9eafafd3f092ba78544afc976aecd4ec9828d219): expose conversion classes and table\n\nAs you may see, I'm a bit lost and undecided, design wise, but I hope it helps to push this further. :)\n",
