    "body": "You are totally right. It must be `const CRPCCommand& command` (passing pointers). I just pulled in your commit.\nI'm also aware that this pointer-passing-approche is not intuitive. But i'm still trying to keep the changeset-size at minimum. I also think a rpc calls will be added when the app starts (modules get loaded) then they stay alive until the app detects a shutdown so the lifetime management tend to be not so complex.\n",
